reviews.review_text:
Great tape! This tape is a wailer! The Nak mix with the 441 is supreme. Really puts you in the bowl at the Omni. The show is great, nice loose jams, long play songs. The second set went past the 100 minute mark and a bunch of people had to flip before Not Fade Away.
The Other One is my all time fave. Phil crunches the shit out of it, they bend around the middle at the 7 minute mark, and then blast right off again....into a Wharf Rat that reminds me why we drove all over the place following these dudes.
Healy had Quad sound at these shows and unless you ran quad mics like this tape (and mine) you didn't get it all..
Put some nice headphones on and crank this one up.
Phil's pounding on this recording, it's great. Thanks.
KEO, email me at akg451ck8@yahoo.com I want to send you my masters...
Thanks Baker and Keo.
PS of all the Not Fade Away's I heard/saw, they really meant it at this show...
